                                            <hr class="a-author__separator a-author__separator--date">
                                            <div class="a-author__article-date">Monday 2 March 2020</div>
                                </aside>                            </aside>



                            <div class='a-body__content has-bbcode'>
                                






    <figure class="bb-figure bb-figure--landscape bb-figure--custom bb-figure--internal">
        <div class="bb-figure__wrapper" style="padding-top:66.7%">
                        <img src="/static/img/tiny.gif" data-src="https://wi-images.condecdn.net/image/wyWVoKZZJab/crop/405/f/wired-floorplan-toilers.jpg" data-srcset="https://wi-images.condecdn.net/image/wyWVoKZZJab/crop/405/f/wired-floorplan-toilers.jpg 405w, https://wi-images.condecdn.net/image/wyWVoKZZJab/crop/810/f/wired-floorplan-toilers.jpg 810w, https://wi-images.condecdn.net/image/wyWVoKZZJab/crop/1020/f/wired-floorplan-toilers.jpg 1020w, https://wi-images.condecdn.net/image/wyWVoKZZJab/crop/1440/f/wired-floorplan-toilers.jpg 1440w, https://wi-images.condecdn.net/image/wyWVoKZZJab/crop/1620/f/wired-floorplan-toilers.jpg 1620w" data-sizes="auto" class="c-image c-image--lazyload "  />
                        <noscript>
                            <img src="https://wi-images.condecdn.net/image/wyWVoKZZJab/crop/405/f/wired-floorplan-toilers.jpg" class=""   />
                        </noscript>
        </div>
        <div class="bb-figure__content">
                <div class="bb-figure__credit">Getty Images / WIRED</div>
        </div>
    </figure>






<p class="bb-p">Hidden within almost every single office, there is an anonymous person spoken about in whispers: someone whose toilet behaviour is so heinous that they garner nicknames like “phantom pooer” or “wet bandit”.</p><p class="bb-p">Many are concerned that with the introduction of unisex bathrooms, these disgusting people could soon be given free rein to unleash their bad habits on entire businesses. And this could be having a not insignificant impact on bathroom use.</p><aside class="ad__main is-hidden ad--article ad--article-rail ad--article-rail-top stick-wrapper ">
    <div class="ad__block stick-element">
            <h5 class="ad__title">Advertisement</h5>
        <div class="da__container"
            data-ad-unit="business-politics/articles"
            data-ad-zone="/5574/uk.n5574.wired"
            data-ad-lazyload="True"
            data-ad-sizes="[[300, 600], [300, 250]]"
            data-ad-bidding="True"
            data-ad-sizemap="null"
            data-ad-position="article-top"
            data-ad-values="{&quot;doctype&quot;: &quot;article&quot;, &quot;uk-wi-tags&quot;: [&quot;Work Smarter&quot;, &quot;Business&quot;]}"
            data-ad-placement="ARTICLE_RAIL_TOP"
            data-ad-group="roadblock"
            data-ad-order="1"
            
        ></div>
    </div>
</aside><p class="bb-p">Gender neutral toilets have really taken off in recent years. Google and Facebook were among the big tech companies in the UK to join employers like WeWork, the BBC, Channel 4, Lloyds of London, Barclays, RBS, Wagamama, HSBC and the British Army in offering unisex bathrooms. </p><p class="bb-p">Many more companies are considering whether to follow their lead and turn their toilets into gender neutral spaces, to become more inclusive to the transgender community and respond to lobbying. But the stakes are high: the massive backlash that some redesigns have already had show that these efforts can create new problems.</p><aside class="a-sidebar-content">
        <h4 class="a-sidebar-content__title">Read next</h4>
        <ul class="a-sidebar-content__list">
                <li class="a-sidebar-content__list-item">
                        <article class="c-card c-card--portrait-small">
                        		<a href="/article/everything-zoom-needs-to-fix" class="c-card__link c-card__link--article ">All the things that Zoom needs to fix right now</a>

                        	<div class="c-card__obj">
                        		<div class="c-card__obj__header">
                        			<div class="c-card__images">

                        						<div class="c-card__image c-card__image--square ">
                        								        <img src="/static/img/tiny.gif" data-src="https://wi-images.condecdn.net/image/ppoyvbL1P83/crop/200/square/f/wired-zoom-fix.jpg" data-srcset="https://wi-images.condecdn.net/image/ppoyvbL1P83/crop/200/square/f/wired-zoom-fix.jpg 200w, https://wi-images.condecdn.net/image/ppoyvbL1P83/crop/300/square/f/wired-zoom-fix.jpg 300w, https://wi-images.condecdn.net/image/ppoyvbL1P83/crop/400/square/f/wired-zoom-fix.jpg 400w, https://wi-images.condecdn.net/image/ppoyvbL1P83/crop/600/square/f/wired-zoom-fix.jpg 600w" data-sizes="auto" class="c-image c-image--lazyload "  />
                        								        <noscript>
                        								            <img src="https://wi-images.condecdn.net/image/ppoyvbL1P83/crop/200/square/f/wired-zoom-fix.jpg" class=""   />
                        								        </noscript>

                        						</div>



                        			</div>
                        		</div>

                        		<div class="c-card__obj__body">
                        			<div class="c-card__header">

                        					<h3 class="c-card__title">
                        					    <span>All the things that Zoom needs to fix right now</span>
                        					</h3>


                        				<hr class="c-card__separator" />
                        			</div>

                        			<div class="c-card__footer">

                        				        <p class="c-card__byline">
                        				            <span class="c-card__byline-prefix">By</span>
                        				            <span class="c-card__byline-name">Sophia Epstein</span>
                        				        </p>

                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </article>                </li>
        </ul>
</aside><p class="bb-p">In 2018, female <a href="https://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-6065075/Female-Home-Office-employees-refusing-use-new-36-000-gender-neutral-toilets.html" class="bb-a">Home Office employees refused to use brand new £36,000 gender neutral toilets</a> when they were first introduced because they kept on walking in on male colleagues using the toilet with the door open. A notice had to be placed outside the unisex toilets at the government department to stop this behaviour, stating: “Women are finding use of the toilets quite distressing and are not using these toilets as a result.”</p><p class="bb-p"><a href="https://blogs.spectator.co.uk/2019/10/the-old-vics-gender-neutral-toilets-leave-women-worse-off/" class="bb-a">The Old Vic theatre in London came under fire last year</a> for converting all of its male and female bathrooms into gender-neutral spaces, a move that it claimed would multiply the amount of toilets that women could use. In fact, the system had blocks labelled “stalls only” and blocks containing urinals – and women were expected to somehow use both.</p><aside class="ad__main is-hidden ad--article ad--article-inline  ">
    <div class="ad__block ">
            <h5 class="ad__title">Advertisement</h5>
        <div class="da__container"
            data-ad-unit="business-politics/articles"
            data-ad-zone="/5574/uk.n5574.wired"
            data-ad-lazyload="True"
            data-ad-sizes="[[100, 100]]"
            data-ad-bidding="False"
            data-ad-sizemap="null"
            data-ad-position="article-middle"
            data-ad-values="{&quot;doctype&quot;: &quot;article&quot;, &quot;uk-wi-tags&quot;: [&quot;Work Smarter&quot;, &quot;Business&quot;]}"
            data-ad-placement="ARTICLE_TEAD"
            
            
            
        ></div>
    </div>
</aside><p class="bb-p">The fundamental problem is toilet design. There are no rules on what exactly makes a bathroom gender neutral, or how to stop the problems identified in single-sex bathrooms becoming widespread in unisex environments. <a href="https://www.express.co.uk/news/uk/943381/gender-neutral-toilets-ladies-gents-urinals-banned-equality-law-lgbtq-transgender-rights" class="bb-a">Employers could be accused of discriminatory behaviour</a> if they designate that a toilet is for specific use for men or women. But if they change all bathrooms to become gender neutral, they could face claims on grounds of safety or religious discrimination. </p><p class="bb-p">Even super loos – self-contained toilet cubicles that have washing facilities – could still fall foul of other regulations to provide for religious people who cannot share toilets with the opposite sex, says Jane Simpson, an architect and access consultant. </p><p class="bb-p">Caught amid these conundrums, companies have struck out on their own and created a hodgepodge of design gaffes: from simply changing signs on the doors, to not bothering to get rid of urinals in gender neutral spaces or designating the disabled toilet as gender neutral. This could lead to problems: women being forced to walk around urinals, put up with appalling toilet etiquette and suffer longer queues – all scenarios that have already happened in public spaces – and could easily seep into the workplace. </p><aside class="a-sidebar-content">
        <h4 class="a-sidebar-content__title">Read next</h4>
        <ul class="a-sidebar-content__list">
                <li class="a-sidebar-content__list-item">
                        <article class="c-card c-card--portrait-small">
                        		<a href="/article/coronavirus-annoying-colleagues" class="c-card__link c-card__link--article ">Coronavirus could trap us with our most annoying colleagues forever</a>

                        	<div class="c-card__obj">
                        		<div class="c-card__obj__header">
                        			<div class="c-card__images">

                        						<div class="c-card__image c-card__image--square ">
                        								        <img src="/static/img/tiny.gif" data-src="https://wi-images.condecdn.net/image/X7zJK0W0ARd/crop/200/square/f/wired-slack-colleague.jpg" data-srcset="https://wi-images.condecdn.net/image/X7zJK0W0ARd/crop/200/square/f/wired-slack-colleague.jpg 200w, https://wi-images.condecdn.net/image/X7zJK0W0ARd/crop/300/square/f/wired-slack-colleague.jpg 300w, https://wi-images.condecdn.net/image/X7zJK0W0ARd/crop/400/square/f/wired-slack-colleague.jpg 400w, https://wi-images.condecdn.net/image/X7zJK0W0ARd/crop/600/square/f/wired-slack-colleague.jpg 600w" data-sizes="auto" class="c-image c-image--lazyload "  />
                        								        <noscript>
                        								            <img src="https://wi-images.condecdn.net/image/X7zJK0W0ARd/crop/200/square/f/wired-slack-colleague.jpg" class=""   />
                        								        </noscript>

                        						</div>



                        			</div>
                        		</div>

                        		<div class="c-card__obj__body">
                        			<div class="c-card__header">

                        					<h3 class="c-card__title">
                        					    <span>Coronavirus could trap us with our most annoying colleagues forever</span>
                        					</h3>


                        				<hr class="c-card__separator" />
                        			</div>

                        			<div class="c-card__footer">

                        				        <p class="c-card__byline">
                        				            <span class="c-card__byline-prefix">By</span>
                        				            <span class="c-card__byline-name">Thomas Hobbs</span>
                        				        </p>

                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </article>                </li>
        </ul>
</aside><p class="bb-p">New office buildings follow the <a href="http://www.bco.org.uk/Research/BestPracticeGuides/Guide-to-Specification.aspx" class="bb-a">British Council for Offices guidance</a>, which does not specifically call for gender neutral bathrooms – instead, it details the requirements for separate rooms for men and women and the ratios of facilities for each sex. There is little guidance for how current single sex toilets should look either: stall architecture in the UK can vary from floor to ceiling doors (or fully enclosed) to those with a large gap at the top and the bottom. In the US, the door can start a foot from the ground. Few conventional toilets are designed to be wide enough to allow a wheelchair user enough space to use them either. And already, there is disparity between the number of toilets that should be allocated to men and women.</p><aside class="ad__main is-hidden ad--article ad--article-inline  ">
    <div class="ad__block ">
            <h5 class="ad__title">Advertisement</h5>
        <div class="da__container"
            data-ad-unit="business-politics/articles"
            data-ad-zone="/5574/uk.n5574.wired"
            data-ad-lazyload="True"
            data-ad-sizes="[[300, 250], [300, 600], [420, 160], [728, 90], [970, 90], [970, 250]]"
            data-ad-bidding="True"
            data-ad-sizemap="[[[0, 0], [[300, 250], [300, 600], [420, 160]]], [[700, 0], [[420, 160]]], [[728, 0], [[728, 90], [420, 160]]], [[970, 0], [[728, 90], [970, 90], [970, 250], [420, 160]]], [[1024, 0], [[420, 160]]]]"
            data-ad-position="article-middle"
            data-ad-values="{&quot;doctype&quot;: &quot;article&quot;, &quot;uk-wi-tags&quot;: [&quot;Work Smarter&quot;, &quot;Business&quot;]}"
            data-ad-placement="ARTICLE_INCONTENT"
            data-ad-group="roadblock"
            data-ad-order="3"
            
        ></div>
    </div>
</aside><p class="bb-p">There are “historic assumptions about the numbers of toilets required by men and women that do not wholly reflect the diversity of the workforce”, says Hywel Davies, technical director at the Chartered Institution of Building Services Engineers. </p><p class="bb-p"><a href="https://www.rsph.org.uk/our-work/policy/healthy-places/taking-the-p.html" class="bb-a">A 2019 report from the Royal Society for Public Health</a> showed how large that gap is: its call for the fair provision of public toilets for women, specified the need for two per every male toilet.</p><p class="bb-p">Yet gender neutral toilets could be the unexpected solution to long queues for the women’s bathroom, argues Luc Bovens, a professor at the University of California. Research that he conducted alongside fellow academic Alexandru Marcoci showed that if a company has 30 employees (15 male and 15 female), the toilet waiting time is about two and a half times longer for women than for men. </p><p class="bb-p">At 300 employees (150 male and 150 female), it is about nine times longer. They argue that allowing men and women to share toilet space meant a dramatic decrease in wait time for women. If all stalls were gender-neutral, then the average waiting time for every person (male or female) would drop to one minute, which is a 20 second increase for men and a one minute, 20 second decrease for women.</p><aside class="a-sidebar-content">
        <h4 class="a-sidebar-content__title">Read next</h4>
        <ul class="a-sidebar-content__list">
                <li class="a-sidebar-content__list-item">
                        <article class="c-card c-card--portrait-small">
                        		<a href="/article/zoom-work-communication" class="c-card__link c-card__link--article ">What the rise of Zoom reveals about how we talk to colleagues</a>

